</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="col clear facility">
<div class="col three-sm">
<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxy38812ac03cfb4f2ba06c302e810ef43e-2">Accommodation</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="yes">Access to TV<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Internet access<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Public telephone<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="no">Family accommodation<span class="hidden"> (no)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Mobile phones permitted<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="no">Private rooms only<span class="hidden"> (no)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Single sex accommodation only<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContentb4f1707455894d13a87c537f3148a452">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="Pilgrim Hospital, Boston" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column3Content_column3Content_FacilityGroupsRepeater_ctl01_FacilityGroupModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=685" style="border-width:0px;"/>
</div>
</div>
<p>This hospital provides most inpatient services from an imposing 9-storey tower block, which also houses theatres and a number of administrative offices.<br/>In addition, there is a recently-refurbished Outpatients Department and recently-constructed state-of-the-art A&amp;E Department and Breast Unit, as well as other buildings including a Medical Education Centre and the Bostonian Private Hospital.<br/>The hospital has 20 wards, which are mainly laid out in four-bed bays. In total there are 391 beds.</p>
</div>
<div class="col two-sm last">
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="col clear facility">
<div class="col three-sm">
